==English==
===Etymology===
From the character of Alex Forrest, played by [[w:Glenn Close|Glenn Close]] in the 1987 film [[w:Fatal Attraction|Fatal Attraction]], who exacted revenge by killing the family pet rabbit, and leaving it boiling on the stove to be found by the family of the boyfriend.

===Noun===
'''bunny boiler'''
:'''''slang'''''

# A person who responds to the end of a relationship in a most extreme manner.
# By extension, any person with that reputation.
# Extremely [[obsessive]] girlfriend, though it is often used with humour when discussing an unhealthily (or annoyingly) needy girlfriend. 

